        <lcObjectives>
            <lcObjectivesGroup id="lcObjectivesGroup_tvl_vbh_1t">
                <lcObjective>Understand the use of the &lt;result>, &lt;example>, and &lt;postreq>
                    elements.</lcObjective>
            </lcObjectivesGroup>
        </lcObjectives>
        <lcDuration>
            <lcTime value="45"/>
        </lcDuration>
        <lcInstruction>
            <p>After youâ€™ve added the steps, you can use three additional elements to complete the
                description of the task:</p>
            <ul id="ul_rp1_w5w_mt">
                <li>&lt;result> describes the result of having successfully performed the task</li>
                <li>&lt;example> shows an example of the entire task</li>
                <li>&lt;postreq> (postrequisites) tells what to do next</li>
            </ul>
            <note>This lesson covers basic use of these elements. For the full specifications for
                    each element, see the <xref
                        href="https://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/dita/v1.3/errata01/os/complete/part3-all-inclusive/langRef/technicalContent/task.html#task"
                        format="html" scope="external">OASIS DITA Version 1.3 Standard - Task</xref>.
            </note>
        </lcInstruction>
